## Motivation

When a Discord bot sends a multi-part reply and one section contains an inline tool error, users only see the error line — all subsequent recommendations and next steps are silently dropped. This makes it impossible for users to see the full agent response. The root cause is in `sanitizeUserFacingText`, which is channel-agnostic and affects all channel types, not just Discord.

## Real behavior proof (required for external PRs)

- **Behavior addressed**: Assistant reply text containing an error-prefix line followed by multi-line user-visible prose was replaced entirely with a templated error label, losing recommendations/next steps. Additionally, raw stack frames (including colon-bearing `node:internal/...`, `file:///...`, async V8 frames, and Windows drive-letter paths) and JSON error payloads could leak into channel replies.

- **Real environment tested**: Linux x64, Node 24.13.1, branch `fix/sanitize-error-context-96007`, commit `73f84cf0e6f`

